308
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:13,800
<i>How well will the individual
American soldier...</i>

309
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:15,480
<i>stand up here in Vietnam?</i>

310
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:18,840
- <i>I’ve never seen anything like--</i>
- What do you think? About that.

311
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:22,680
I don’t know.
13,000 miles....

312
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:25,440
That’s a long way
to go to fight a war.

313
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:28,680
<i>The Vietcong, they fought
the French and the Japanese for 30 years.</i>

314
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:30,680
<i>Do you really think
they can be weeded out?</i>

315
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:34,040
<i>I think that anything that lives in a cave
can be weeded out.</i>

316
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:39,200
I just hope they send to
to Europe or Korea or...

317
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:41,200
- They can’t.
- Some place safe.

318
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:43,520
Every Marine has a tour of duty there.

319
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:45,280
It’s not like the Army.

320
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:47,520
What’s the matter with you, anyway?

321
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:50,560
- You served. Uncle Bob served.
- I know, Ronnie. I know.

322
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,720
Don’t you remember what
President Kennedy said?

323
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:54,880
"There’s not gonna be
an America anymore...

324
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:57,360
"unless there are people
who are willing to sacrifice."

325
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:00,120
- I love my country.
- I know.

326
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:03,200
And you’re right Ronnie.
You’re doing the right thing.

327
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:05,480
Communism has to be stopped.

328
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:08,280
It’s God’s will you go.
We’re proud of you.

329
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:10,560
Be careful, that’s all.

330
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:14,600
<i>Up there in Hanoi they don’t allow
magazines and newspapers, televisions...</i>

331
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:17,440
<i>to cast doubts on the military system.</i>

332
00:23:17,720 --> 00:23:20,640
Don’t you know what it means to me
to be a Marine, Dad?

333
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:25,080
Ever since I was a kid, I’ve wanted this.
I wanted to serve my country.

334
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:26,880
And I want to go.

335
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:29,080
I want to go to Vietnam...

336
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:31,720
and I’ll die there if I have to.

337
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:38,240
<i>The attitude of people on the home front
is very important.</i>

338
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:40,520
Not a nice night for the prom.

339
00:23:56,680 --> 00:23:58,920
Sometimes, God, I’m so confused.

340
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:03,880
Sometimes I think I’d just...

341
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:06,880
like to stay here in Massapequa...

342
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:09,600
and never Ieave...

343
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:13,280
but I got to go.

344
00:24:18,840 --> 00:24:22,040
Help me, Jesus.
Help me to make the right decision.

345
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:25,760
<i>Please, dear God.</i>

346
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,320
Ron.

347
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:55,320
Ronnie, what happened to you?

348
00:25:10,360 --> 00:25:12,760
What....
Oh, jeez.

349
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:16,200
- Donna.
- Ronnie.

350
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:18,400
Will you dance with me?

351
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:22,520
Yes. Sure.

352
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:52,960
Near the Cua Viet River, Vietnam
October 1967

353
00:26:53,240 --> 00:26:55,520
<i>You have beaucoup gooks.
They’re coming at you.</i>

354
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:57,280
<i>Echo-1’s pushing them. Over.</i>

355
00:26:57,400 --> 00:27:00,000
6, 2-Actual.
Sit Rep as follows.

356
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:03,480
<i>Two set in on the beach.
The tracks are moving this way. Over.</i>

357
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:06,080
Sounds like beaucoup gooks in there.

358
00:27:06,840 --> 00:27:09,360
I got a feeling I’m finally going
to get to see one.

359
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:11,200
Relax, you’ll be all right.

360
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,280
Where you from, Wilson?

361
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:16,600
First Battalion, 9th Motor T.
Mostly around Danang.

362
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:19,520
The Sergeant Major said the grunts
needed replacements...

363
00:27:19,560 --> 00:27:21,480
so they took me out of battalion supply.

364
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:24,480
- Where are you from in the world?
- Venus, Georgia.

365
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:27,680
This is my second tour.
I haven’t seen a Georgia boy get hurt yet.

366
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:30,240
You’ll be all right.

367
00:27:35,560 --> 00:27:38,560
Echo-1’s taken in,
coming northwest edge of the ville.

368
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:41,920
We got gooks moving this way.

369
00:27:42,560 --> 00:27:45,160
Look out there, Sergeant.
Can you see them?

370
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:48,160
Right there. You see them?
They got rifles.

371
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:51,840
<i>Can you see the rifles?
Right there. You see them?</i>

372
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:55,560
<i>Can you see the rifles?</i>

373
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:57,160
Yes, sir.

374
00:27:58,400 --> 00:28:00,440
Pass the word.
When I give the order...

375
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:03,480
I want to light up this ville
like a motherfucking Christmas tree.

376
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:07,040
I think we got them! This time I think
we fucking got them! Move out.

377
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:08,840
Pass the word.
Fire on my command.

378
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:10,560
Wilson, come with me.

379
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:13,720
Cover that big hooch.
Fire on my command! Pass the word.

380
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:16,960
Corporal, start ranking.
Fire on my command.

381
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:18,840
Fire on my command.

382
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:22,360
Cease fire. Cease fire, you asshole.

383
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:24,600
What the fuck are you doing?

384
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:28,840
Cease fire.

385
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:30,920
What happened?

386
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:33,480
Cease fire, you asshole.

387
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:35,200
I want to know what happened.

388
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:37,720
I don’t know, sir.
Possible accidental discharge, sir.

389
00:28:37,760 --> 00:28:41,760
We better get a sweep team in there.
Take five men. Tell me how many we got.

390
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:42,920
Yes, sir.

391
00:28:43,800 --> 00:28:46,560
Motherfucker!
Baldy, on me.

392
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:50,800
Brooks! Martinez! On me!
Wilson, on me!

393
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:54,040
Line.

394
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:01,360
<i>Standby.</i>

395
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:05,880
<i>Target: 15,637 meters.</i>

396
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:08,360
<i>Direction: 5800.</i>

397
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:18,520
Get him out!

398
00:29:20,320 --> 00:29:22,400
Check it out over there.
Everything out.

399
00:29:22,520 --> 00:29:25,760
Baldy, get everything out.
Baldy! There! Check it out.

400
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:34,840
Get him out!

401
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:42,520
Oh, my God.

402
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:45,720
We didn’t do this, did we?

403
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:48,680
- Oh, my God.
- Jesus Christ.

404
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:58,400
2-Actual, 2, better get down here quick,
and bring the corpsmen.

405
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:01,640
We got beaucoup wounded.
Civilians.

406
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:03,680
Martinez, help me!

407
00:30:06,720 --> 00:30:10,880
We wasted them.
Motherfucker! We wasted them!

408
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:27,640
Where are the rifles?

409
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:29,920
Where are the rifles?

410
00:30:30,040 --> 00:30:32,120
There ain’t no fucking rifles.

411
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:36,160
Jesus fucking Christ!
Well, help him, then.

412
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:38,200
Help him!

413
00:30:38,280 --> 00:30:39,560
Motherfuck!

414
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:41,240
- Fucking great.
- Shit!

415
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:43,720
Get up and help him.
I want you to help him.

416
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:44,840
Forgive us.

417
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:46,680
Help me.
Somebody help me!

418
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:52,320
6, 2-Actual.
Request emergency medevac.

419
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:54,840
We got a lot of friendly wounded. Over.

420
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:58,400
<i>Negative. Get out of there! Leave
the wounded! You got Arty inbound!</i>

421
00:30:58,520 --> 00:30:59,920
<i>Get out!</i>

422
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:02,240
Get back to the dunes.

423
00:31:02,440 --> 00:31:05,320
We got gooks in the ville.
I want you moving out of here.

424
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:07,880
Get out. Move out.
That’s a direct order.

425
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:09,600
I want you out that door.

426
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:15,320
It wasn’t your fault, god damn it!
They got in the goddamned way!

427
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:20,000
Kovic, get your fucking ass up.
We gotta move! We got gooks in the ville.

428
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:23,320
- The baby.
- Move out. Get back.

429
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:26,800
- The baby.
- No, move. Now. Let’s move.

430
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:32,040
Move out!
Get the fuck up! Move!

431
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:34,960
The ville is going to blow!
Arty’s on the way.

432
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:57,960
Red, Abbot.

433
00:32:26,360 --> 00:32:28,120
<i>Wilson’s hit.</i>

434
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:09,720
What happened?

435
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:49,360
X.O., Sergeant Kovic here
to see you, sir.

436
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:51,520
Stand easy, Sergeant.

437
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:57,400
Yeah, Kovic. Lieutenant told me
that was a pretty rough time.

438
00:33:57,440 --> 00:33:59,360
Yes, sir. It was pretty bad.

439
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:02,880
- Ran into a few of them, didn’t you?
- Yes, sir.

440
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:07,160
You want to see me
about something, Sergeant?

441
00:34:07,240 --> 00:34:08,480
Yes, sir.

442
00:34:08,640 --> 00:34:12,800
Like I said to the captain, sir,
it was a very confusing day.

443
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:17,000
- The villagers--
- Yeah. I know about the villagers.

444
00:34:18,160 --> 00:34:20,680
- The villagers--
- It was very, very unfortunate.

445
00:34:22,120 --> 00:34:24,920
- The enemy used them as cover.
- Yes, sir.

446
00:34:25,960 --> 00:34:30,240
They popped up, started firing.
We were running back. And it was real glary.

447
00:34:31,640 --> 00:34:34,720
Very confusing,
and that’s when it happened, sir.

448
00:34:35,320 --> 00:34:36,560
What happened?

449
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:40,440
- Sir, that was when Wilson was killed, sir.
- I know about Wilson.

450
00:34:41,240 --> 00:34:42,680
Sir, you see...

451
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:46,880
he was the last one out,
and that’s when it happened, sir.

452
00:34:48,880 --> 00:34:51,320
Sir, I think I might
have killed him, sir.

453
00:34:51,880 --> 00:34:53,240
I don’t think so.

454
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:56,520
He was coming up over the dune.
It was very confusing.

455
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:58,400
And I think I might
have killed him.

456
00:34:58,440 --> 00:35:01,960
It’s hard. I was out a couple of weeks ago.
Sometimes it’s...

457
00:35:02,720 --> 00:35:05,120
very hard to tell what’s happening.

458
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:08,080
Yes, sir.

459
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:11,880
But, sir, I think I killed Wilson.

460
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:19,920
I don’t think so, Kovic.

461
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:22,840
But, sir, I want you to know that--

462
00:35:22,880 --> 00:35:26,720
Don’t talk like that. I don’t need anybody
to come in here and tell me this shit.

463
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:29,520
- I’ll take your head off. Is that clear?
- Yes, sir!

464
00:35:30,840 --> 00:35:32,000
All right.

465
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:34,480
Carry on.

466
00:35:39,080 --> 00:35:41,320
X.O. ought to court-martial his ass.

467
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:46,720
Sergeant K.

